                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Sometimes you are forced to follow the mob to stay in range.<br /><br />Also turn pet taunt off your DoTs should do more damage than the pet and when fear wears off mob should come back to you because you are higher than pet on agro list.<br /><br />Best bet is try to stay reletavely close. Do the 5 sec run thing I.E. you sit get tick of mana get up run towards mob for 5 sec sit in time to get tick of mana repeat. As long as you are sitting when the game does the check for mana regen sitting you'll get the med bonus for sitting.<br /><br />A tick is 6 seconds btw.<br /><br />Also try hunting along zone walls the pathing the mob takes feared is different in different parts of the zone.<br /><br />Also sitting raises agro with the mob so if it's close and you are sitting it'll ignore pet to come after you that's a good way to keep it in spell range.<br /><br />Slississ<br />Iksar Necromancer<br />The Nameless<br /><br />"Druids are meant to show us that not everthing in nature has a purpose"<br /><br />Added some things<br /><br />Edited by - Slississ on 10/16/2002  07:31:05</span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
