                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> by pathing i believe they mean watch the path that the mobs take.  there are many areas that have odd pathing and can be used to your advantage.  places where mobs turn around whenever they are hit by melee or DD damage; places where a mob will run into a wall (100% legal by the way as long as when fear wears off the mob isn't stuck in the wall); places where a mob just doesn't run near others ones, etc...<br /><br />as for the being out of range...do you mean that after you darkness and fear they run out of range?  you just need to follow them, until lvl 29 when you get a darkness with decent snare.  or group with a druid, i believe they get decent snares pretty low.<br /><br /><br /><br /><a href="http://www.theinverselogic.com/"><br />Abillister "Monkey" Abu - Inverse Logic<br /><img src="http://www.finitesite.com/yenmabek/10372061.jpg"></a></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
